HEADWORD: man-of-war bird
<hw>man-of-war bird</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <def>The
frigate bird, a long-billed warm-water seabird with wide wingspan and
forked tail; also applied to the skua gulls, and to the wandering
albatross.</def>⟦br⟧
